The paper deals with audio signal processing and machine learning techniques for source separation. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.SI (Speech and Natural Language Processing) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses generative adversarial networks (GANs), which are a popular topic in machine learning research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category. The paper also involves time-frequency analysis, which is a common technique in computer vision and image processing, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses datasets for evaluation, which is a common practice in multimedia research, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category.
